BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:i68UzDIWfORuR39vC2M-w
SUMMARY:TADAIMA: I'm Home
DTSTAMP:20260403T032252Z
DTSTART:20260407T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:After more than 80 years\, a treasured collection returns “home
	” to Seattle’s Japanese American community. In 1942 dozens of traditional 
	Boys’ and Girls’ Day dolls were entrusted to Bailey Gatzert Elementary Sch
	ool by Japanese American families facing forced incarceration. Most were n
	ever reclaimed after the war. Artist Miya Sukune uses recent research in M
	OHAI’s collection\, as well as interviews with Japanese American survivors
	 and their descendants\, to create an installation called “Tadaima\,” mean
	ing “I’m home.”\n\nTADAIMA: “I’m Home!” Bringing Seattle’s Girls’ and Boys
	’ Day Dolls Home reconnects the dolls with their traditional role of prote
	cting and blessing children. It invites visitors to celebrate the resilien
	ce\, memory\, and enduring traditions of the Japanese American Community.\
	n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/tadaima-i-m-home/18096356
	/2026-04-07T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/tadaima-i-m-home/18096356
	/2026-04-07T00
LOCATION:Museum of History and Industry\, 860 Terry Ave N\, Seattle\, Seatt
	le\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:KH0zuJRhM5NTE1IEGsdf0
SUMMARY:Earth Month Event | Mindfulness Walk
DTSTAMP:20260403T032252Z
DTSTART:20260407T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate Earth Month with a Mindfulness Walk in the Park!\n\nT
	aking inspiration from the Japanese idea of shinrin-yoku \\(forest bathin 
	g\\)\, we will be hosting a series of mindfulness walks in Pioneer Park. M
	indfulness walking in the forest has shown to have a myriad of benefits fr
	om  improving heart health to reducing stress \\(https://www.npr.org/2023/
	08/22 /1195337204/a-guide-to-forest-bathing\\).\n\nForest Steward Marilyn 
	Cornwe ll \\(https://www.soulscapes.us/\\) will be leading an hour-long gu
	ided walk t hrough the park. Please join us if your curious about mindfuln
	ess\, want to learn more about and experience healing powers of being in n
	ature\, and/or if you want to deepen your connection with Pioneer Park and
	 others.\n\n When:  Tuesday\, April 4th\, 11am-12pm\n\nWhere: Pioneer Park
	 NW\, Meet at the corner of Island Crest Way and SE 68th St. Follow VOLUNT
	EER EVENT Signs \n\nWhat to bring: Dress for the weather in clothes and sh
	oes you will comfo rtable walking and standing in\, as well as water.\n\nh
	ttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/earth-month-event-mindfulness
	-walk/18066426/2026-04-07T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/earth-month-event-mindful
	ness-walk/18066426/2026-04-07T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
